# Toon Ranks Backend — Cursor Rules

## Project identity
FastAPI + SQLAlchemy async backend for a manga/manhwa/manhua ranking platform.
Python 3.11+, PostgreSQL (schema: man_review), Railway deployment.

## Hard rules
- Never work on `main` — always create a branch
- All database access is async — use `await` on every execute/commit/refresh
- Every ORM model must have `__table_args__ = {"schema": "man_review"}` — omitting this breaks prod
- Use `app.database.get_async_session` as the DB dependency in new routes
- Use `app.deps.admin` for all auth/role guards — never inline role string checks
- Rate-limit any public mutating endpoint using `@limiter.limit()` from `app.limiter`
- Line length: 100. Linter: Ruff (`ruff check .`)

## Patterns to follow
- Router files go in `app/routes/`, registered in `app/main.py` via `app.include_router(...)`
- Pydantic schemas go in `app/schemas/`
- Pure helpers go in `app/utils/`
- Tests go in `tests/`, file name `*_test.py`, use existing `conftest.py` fixtures

## Domain vocabulary
- Series types: MANGA, MANHWA, MANHUA
- Approval states: DRAFT → PENDING → APPROVED
- User roles: GENERAL < CONTRIBUTOR < ADMIN
- Scoring formula: final_score = avg(story, characters, worldbuilding, art, drama_or_fight) — all rated 1-10

## Key reference files
- Data model: docs/DATA_MODEL.md
- All endpoints: docs/API.md
- Conventions: docs/CONVENTIONS.md
- Architecture: docs/ARCHITECTURE.md

## What to avoid
- Sync SQLAlchemy calls inside async functions
- Hardcoded role strings in route logic
- New models without the man_review schema
- Startup schema changes outside of app/main.py on_startup
- Committing/pushing without being asked
